videos.headline: SVP's 'Best Thing I Saw Today': Hodskins scores for Gators
videos.description: Florida walk-on Zach Hodskins, who has only one hand because of a birth defect, scores the first point in his college career against Jacksonville on Tuesday night.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Highlight (SVP's 'Best Thing I Saw Today': Hodskins scores for Gators) 2015/12/23 ESHEET SVP SC

article.description: KeVaughn Allen scored a career-high 15 points, leading four Florida players in double figures, and the Gators beat Jacksonville 89-65 on Tuesday night.

related.description: Walk-on Zach Hodskins, who was born without a hand on his left arm, received a loud ovation after overcoming "an unbelievable adversity" and making his first shot for the Gators.

article.headline: Florida beats Jacksonville 89-65, stays unbeaten at home
article.linkText: Florida beats Jacksonville 89-65, stays unbeaten at home
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Dontarius James tied his career high with 23 points as Jacksonville defeated Florida National 78-69 on Wednesday night. Diante Wood had 18 points and 12 rebounds for Jacksonville (4-2). Mo Arnold added seven rebounds. Jose Benitez had 17 points for the Conquistadors. Jeffery Hernandez added 15 points and eight rebounds. Kenneth Santos had 14 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
